-- IDEA 16: Farm-to-Table Pre-order Platform - Author 11
-- ============================================================
(16, 11, E'# HarvestRoute - Farm-to-Table Pre-order Platform\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nHarvestRoute is a lightweight SaaS platform that enables small-scale organic farmers to list seasonal produce for weekly pre-orders, with customers picking up at designated community spots. The core insight is that farmers markets are a distribution bottleneck: a farmer driving to 3-5 markets every weekend loses 20+ hours per week in logistics that could be replaced by a single digital pre-order window. HarvestRoute creates a direct pre-order channel between farmers and loyal local customers, reducing waste, improving cashflow predictability, and cutting farmers'' market dependency without eliminating it.\n\n**Core Value Proposition**: Sell your harvest before you pick it. Know your numbers on Monday, not Saturday.\n\n**Target**: Organic farmers with 2-5 farmers market stalls, annual revenue $40,000-$150,000, looking to build a stable recurring customer base.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Data | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| US farmers markets (active) | ~8,600 | USDA 2023 |\n| Small-scale organic farms (<50 acres) | ~130,000 | USDA Census of Agriculture |\n| Avg farmer revenue lost to unsold produce | 15-22% | Farm Bureau estimate |\n| Local food market size (US) | $20B | 2023, growing 10%/yr |\n| Avg CSA subscription (weekly) | $25-$45 | Regional variation |\n| Customer willingness to pre-order local food | 68% | FMI Consumer Survey 2023 |\n| Farmers using digital sales tools | <18% | USDA NASS |\n| Target TAM (tool subscriptions) | ~$78M/yr | 130k farms × $600/yr avg |\n\n**Key Trend**: Post-pandemic local food loyalty remains high. 61% of consumers who started buying local in 2020 still do so regularly. Pre-order models (CSA-style) see 40% lower churn than walk-up market sales.\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Type | Pricing | Strengths | Weaknesses |\n|-----------|------|---------|-----------|------------|\n| Farmigo | Farm management + ordering | $50-$150/mo | Full-featured, CSA focused | Complex setup, dated UI |\n| Local Line | Farm e-commerce | $79-$249/mo | Clean interface, B2B capable | Expensive for micro farms |\n| Barn2Door | Direct farm sales | $99-$299/mo | Marketing automation | Overkill for small operations |\n| Shopify + plugins | General e-commerce | $39+/mo + apps | Flexible | No farm/pickup-specific logic |\n| Paper signup sheets | Manual | $0 | Zero learning curve | No automation, no data |\n| **HarvestRoute** | **Farm pre-order** | **$29-$79/mo** | **Pickup-native, zero waste focus** | **New brand** |\n\n**Gap**: No competitor targets the 2-5 market farmer specifically with a mobile-first, pickup-route-optimized tool at sub-$50/month pricing.\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n### Persona A: Sarah - The Weekend Market Regular\n- **Age**: 44, female, Asheville NC\n- **Farm**: 12-acre mixed vegetable and herb farm, certified organic\n- **Markets**: 3 farmers markets (Sat, Sun, Wed)\n- **Revenue**: ~$72,000/yr, 60% from markets\n- **Pain Points**:\n  1. Drives 8+ hours/week to markets, often returns with 20-30% unsold\n  2. Cannot predict which crops will sell well, leading to over/under harvest\n  3. Regulars ask to reserve items but she has no system to manage it\n- **Tech comfort**: Moderate, uses Square for market payments, basic Instagram\n- **Willingness to pay**: $35-$50/month if it saves one market trip per week\n\n### Persona B: Marcus - The CSA Experimenter\n- **Age**: 38, male, Vermont\n- **Farm**: 8-acre vegetable farm, 40-member CSA plus 2 markets\n- **Pain Points**:\n  1. CSA box contents feel rigid - customers want choice, not surprise boxes\n  2. Managing pickup schedule changes is a logistics nightmare via email\n  3. Off-season cashflow gap hurts planning\n- **Goal**: Convert market regulars into flexible pre-order subscribers\n- **Willingness to pay**: $50-$75/month for a system that handles customer comms\n\n### Persona C: Elena - The Scaling Producer\n- **Age**: 52, female, California Central Valley adjacent\n- **Farm**: 28-acre diversified farm, 5 markets, 2 employees\n- **Pain Points**:\n  1. Employee time spent at markets is the #1 cost\n  2. Needs data to make planting decisions based on demand signals\n  3. Wants to offer restaurant pickup routes but has no route management tool\n- **Willingness to pay**: $79-$99/month for multi-location pickup management\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| P0 | Weekly produce listing | Farmer posts available items with quantity caps each week |\n| P0 | Customer pre-order cart | Customers browse and reserve items before cutoff |\n| P0 | Pickup location manager | Set multiple pickup spots with days/times |\n| P0 | Order summary export | PDF/CSV of all orders by pickup location for packing |\n| P0 | Cutoff window settings | Farmer sets order deadline (e.g. Wednesday noon for Saturday pickup) |\n| P1 | SMS/email order reminders | Auto-remind customers before pickup day |\n| P1 | Recurring order subscriptions | Customers set standing weekly orders |\n| P1 | Inventory auto-close | Items auto-close when quantity limit reached |\n| P1 | Stripe payment integration | Collect payment at order time or pickup |\n| P2 | Demand forecasting | Show trending items based on past order velocity |\n| P2 | Route optimization | Suggest efficient pickup spot sequencing |\n| P2 | Wholesale/restaurant portal | Separate ordering tier for bulk buyers |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n```\nFrontend:\n  - Farmer dashboard: Next.js 15 + TailwindCSS (responsive, mobile-first)\n  - Customer ordering page: SSG/ISR for fast load, no login required to browse\n\nBackend:\n  - API: Go + Echo v4 (REST)\n  - Job scheduler: Cron for cutoff enforcement and reminder dispatch\n  - Payment: Stripe Connect (marketplace model, farmer receives directly)\n\nData:\n  - PostgreSQL 16 (orders, inventory, pickup locations)\n  - Redis (session cache, real-time inventory count)\n\nNotifications:\n  - Twilio SMS (order confirmation + pickup reminder)\n  - SendGrid (order receipts, weekly listing announcements)\n\nInfrastructure:\n  - Vercel (frontend) + Fly.io (backend API)\n  - Cloudflare CDN + DDoS protection\n```\n\n**Key Technical Decision**: Inventory is managed as a soft cap with a 2-minute hold on items added to cart, preventing oversell without requiring real-time websockets. Pickup locations are modeled as independent channels so one farm can serve multiple communities.\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Plan | Price | Included | Target |\n|------|-------|---------|--------|\n| Seedling (free) | $0/mo | 1 pickup location, 20 orders/wk | Trial |\n| Grower | $29/mo | 3 pickup locations, unlimited orders | Small farms |\n| Harvest Pro | $59/mo | 10 locations, recurring subs, analytics | Growing farms |\n| Market+ | $99/mo | Unlimited locations, wholesale portal, API | Multi-market farms |\n| Transaction fee | 1.2% + Stripe fees | On all paid orders | All plans |\n\n**Revenue Projection**:\n- Month 6: 120 paid farms, avg $45/mo = $5,400 MRR\n- Month 12: 400 paid farms, avg $52/mo = $20,800 MRR\n- Transaction revenue adds ~$8,000/mo at scale\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Milestone | Timeline | Deliverables | Success Criteria |\n|-----------|----------|-------------|------------------|\n| M1: Foundation | Weeks 1-6 | Farmer listing, customer ordering, pickup management, order export | 5 beta farms live |\n| M2: Payments | Weeks 7-10 | Stripe Connect integration, order confirmation emails | 100% order payment capture |\n| M3: Retention | Weeks 11-14 | SMS reminders, recurring orders, inventory auto-close | 30-day farmer retention >65% |\n| M4: Growth | Weeks 15-20 | Analytics dashboard, wholesale portal, referral program | 80 paying farms, MRR $3,200 |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| Category | KPI | Target (6 months) |\n|----------|-----|-------------------|\n| Adoption | Registered farms | 200 |\n| Activation | Farms with ≥1 live listing | 65% |\n| Retention | Farmer monthly retention | ≥70% |\n| Revenue | MRR | $8,000 |\n| Customer | Orders processed/week | 2,500 |\n| Efficiency | Avg unsold produce rate (farms using app) | <10% |\n| Satisfaction | Farmer NPS | ≥45 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Severity | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|------------|\n| Low tech adoption among older farmers | High | High | Onboarding call included in all paid plans, video walkthroughs |\n| Seasonal revenue drop (winter) | Medium | High | Annual billing discount, off-season features (waitlist, early CSA signup) |\n| Stripe Connect compliance complexity | Medium | Medium | Use verified Stripe Connect Express, pre-built onboarding flow |\n| Customer no-shows at pickup | Medium | Medium | Prepayment option + no-show policy template provided to farmers |\n| Competition from existing farm management suites | High | Low | Stay lean and pickup-native; avoid feature bloat that loses simplicity advantage |',
    E'[{"step":"Problem framing","decision":"Focus on pre-order as the core mechanic, not general farm management","reason":"Farmers already have accounting and field tools - the gap is specifically the pre-order/pickup channel which no lightweight tool serves"},{"step":"Pricing","decision":"$29 entry plan targeting micro farms","reason":"Barn2Door and Local Line start at $99+, leaving the 2-5 market farmer unserved; lower entry point accelerates adoption"},{"step":"Payment model","decision":"Stripe Connect with 1.2% transaction fee on top of subscription","reason":"Transaction fee aligns incentives - we earn more as farmer earns more, justifies ongoing investment in conversion features"},{"step":"Technical scope","decision":"No mobile app in MVP, mobile-optimized web only","reason":"Farmers access from phone browser at market; native app adds 6-8 weeks dev time with little benefit at MVP stage"},{"step":"Customer ordering UX","decision":"No customer account required to browse listings","reason":"Reducing friction for first-time customers is critical; account creation can be deferred to checkout"},{"step":"Go-to-market","decision":"Target farmers market associations as distribution channel","reason":"Each association reaches 30-80 member farms; a single partnership outperforms months of individual outreach"}]',
    'submitted', 42, NOW() - INTERVAL '18 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '19 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '18 days'),

