(17, 24, E'# PlannerStack - All-in-One Workflow for Independent Wedding Planners\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nPlannerStack is a unified workflow platform for independent wedding planners managing 15-30 weddings per year. Rather than optimizing for a single workflow piece (like client portals or timeline builders), PlannerStack takes a "planner operating system" approach: one tool that handles the entire arc from first client inquiry through post-wedding vendor review. The key differentiator is an intelligent timeline engine that auto-suggests standard wedding milestones based on wedding date, guest count, and service level, dramatically reducing the setup time per new client.\n\n**Value Proposition**: Set up a new client in under 15 minutes. Never let a deadline slip. Get paid faster.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Data | Source |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| US weddings annually | ~2.0M | The Knot |\n| Weddings with professional planner | ~540,000 (27%) | The Knot |\n| Independent planners (non-franchise) | ~45,000 | WIPA |\n| Planners reporting tool fragmentation as top pain | 67% | Planner survey N=120 |\n| Avg tools used per planner (spreadsheets, email, PM app) | 4.2 | Survey |\n| Time lost to tool-switching per wedding | ~3 hrs | Estimate |\n| Planners willing to pay for unified tool | 71% | Survey |\n| Software TAM (independent planners) | ~$54M/yr | 45k × $1,200 avg |\n\n**Market timing**: 2024 saw a 14% increase in weddings vs. 2019 baseline, creating backlog pressure for planners who are managing more events with the same (or fewer) support staff. This pressure accelerates willingness to adopt tools that reduce admin overhead.\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Strength | Weakness | Price/mo |\n|-----------|---------|---------|----------|\n| Aisle Planner | Wedding-specific, established | Outdated UI, slow mobile | $49-$99 |\n| Honeybook | Great CRM + proposals | Weak timeline, not wedding-native | $16-$66 |\n| Planning Pod | Comprehensive | Built for venues, complex UI | $49-$199 |\n| Tave | Photography/event focus | Not planner-workflow native | $21-$99 |\n| 17hats | General service business | No wedding logic | $45/mo |\n| **PlannerStack** | **Planner-native + smart timeline** | **New brand** | **$55-$95** |\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n### Persona A: Jessica - The Growth-Stage Planner\n- **Age**: 31, female, Atlanta GA\n- **Volume**: 18 weddings/year, targeting 25\n- **Current state**: Uses Honeybook for proposals, Aisle Planner for timelines, Google Sheets for budgets, Gmail for everything else\n- **Core frustration**: Information about each wedding lives in 4 different tools; finding anything requires switching apps\n- **What she wants**: One place where everything for a wedding lives\n- **Price tolerance**: $65-$75/month; considers it an investment in professional growth\n\n### Persona B: Tom - The Veteran with Volume\n- **Age**: 49, male, Chicago IL\n- **Volume**: 30 weddings/year, runs a one-person operation\n- **Current state**: Has built elaborate Google Sheets templates over 10 years; considers himself "good at systems"\n- **Core frustration**: As volume grew, his manual system started breaking — he missed a vendor payment deadline last spring\n- **What he wants**: Automated deadline reminders that he doesn''t have to set manually for every wedding\n- **Killer feature**: Smart timeline that auto-populates deadlines based on wedding date\n- **Price tolerance**: $75-$95/month if it prevents one costly error\n\n### Persona C: Sofia - The Partial-Planning Specialist\n- **Age**: 27, female, Miami FL\n- **Volume**: 22 weddings/year, partial planning only (couples do venue/catering, she does coordination)\n- **Core frustration**: Getting handed over weddings mid-planning with incomplete information, no standardized handoff format\n- **What she wants**: A standardized intake process that captures all critical wedding info upfront; vendor confirmation tracking\n- **Price tolerance**: $55/month, values simplicity over features\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| P0 | Smart timeline engine | Auto-generates milestone schedule based on wedding date + service type + guest count |\n| P0 | Vendor management hub | Contact book + contract status + payment schedule per vendor |\n| P0 | Budget tracker | Estimated vs. actual with payment status and due date alerts |\n| P0 | Client portal | Progress view for couples: milestones, to-dos, confirmed vendors |\n| P0 | Automated deadline reminders | Email alerts for upcoming vendor payments, client decisions |\n| P1 | Proposal + e-signature | Send planning proposals, collect signatures in-app |\n| P1 | Document vault | Per-wedding storage for contracts, inspiration, venue docs |\n| P1 | Day-of run sheet | Exportable minute-by-minute timeline for ceremony and reception |\n| P1 | Multi-wedding calendar | Master view across all active weddings |\n| P2 | Vendor review system | Post-wedding vendor rating for planner''s private reference |\n| P2 | Client referral portal | Automated post-wedding review request to couples |\n| P2 | Team assistant access | Limited account for assistants |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n```\nBackend:\n  - Go + Echo v4 (RESTful API)\n  - Timeline engine: Rule-based milestone generator\n    - Input: wedding_date, service_type, guest_count, venue_type\n    - Output: pre-populated milestone list with suggested due dates\n    - Planner edits/overrides any auto-generated item\n  - Cron jobs: Daily deadline check, reminder dispatch\n  - PDF generation: headless Chrome via Puppeteer (day-of run sheet)\n\nFrontend:\n  - Planner UI: Next.js 15 + TailwindCSS\n  - Client portal: Separate Next.js app at client.plannerstack.com\n  - Drag-and-drop timeline: dnd-kit\n\nData:\n  - PostgreSQL 16 (weddings, vendors, timeline events, documents)\n  - Redis (sessions, reminder queue)\n  - AWS S3 (documents and contracts)\n\nAuth:\n  - Planner: Email/password + Google OAuth\n  - Couples: Magic link (no account)\n  - E-signatures: Dropbox Sign API\n\nNotifications:\n  - SendGrid (deadline reminders, weekly status digest)\n```\n\n**Smart Timeline Engine Detail**: The engine stores a library of ~120 standard wedding milestones (e.g., "Book florist — typically 10 months before wedding date"). On client creation, the planner selects service type and the engine pre-populates a milestone set, which the planner then trims and customizes. This reduces new client setup from 45 minutes to 12 minutes.\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Plan | Price | Active Weddings | Highlights |\n|------|-------|----------------|------------|\n| Starter | $55/mo | 15 active | Core workflow, client portal, auto-reminders |\n| Pro | $79/mo | 30 active | + proposals, e-sign, document vault, run sheet |\n| Studio | $95/mo | Unlimited | + team access, analytics, vendor review system |\n| Annual (all) | 2 months free | — | Billed annually |\n\n**Gross margin target**: >82% (SaaS, primary costs are hosting, SendGrid, Dropbox Sign per-signature fees)\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Milestone | Timeframe | Deliverables | Success Gate |\n|-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| M1: Core engine | 6 weeks | Smart timeline, vendor hub, budget tracker | 12 beta planners actively using |\n| M2: Client portal | 3 weeks | Couple progress view, magic link, deadline reminders | Couple login rate ≥60% |\n| M3: Proposals | 3 weeks | Proposal builder, e-signature via Dropbox Sign | First paid proposal sent |\n| M4: Launch | 4 weeks | Billing, onboarding flow, referral program | 50 paying planners |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | 6-Month Target | 12-Month Target |\n|-----|---------------|----------------|\n| Registered planners | 600 | 2,000 |\n| Paid planners | 200 | 700 |\n| MRR | $14,000 | $52,000 |\n| Avg setup time per new wedding | <15 min | <10 min |\n| Deadline miss rate (on platform) | <1% | <0.5% |\n| Monthly churn | <3.5% | <2.5% |\n| NPS | ≥50 | ≥60 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Severity | Probability | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|-------------|------------|\n| Smart timeline generates wrong milestones | High | Medium | Planner always reviews and edits; engine is a starting point, not final word |\n| Data import from Aisle Planner is complex | Medium | High | Build CSV importer for vendor list and budget; full migration not required |\n| Planner loyalty to current tools is high | High | High | Free 60-day trial, no credit card required; zero migration required to start |\n| E-signature liability concerns | Medium | Low | Use Dropbox Sign (legal compliance included); provide terms template |\n| Scope creep from feature requests | High | High | Public roadmap with voting; ship monthly; no custom enterprise work |',
    E'[{"step":"Core differentiator","decision":"Build the smart timeline engine as the primary hook","reason":"Every planner we interviewed cited timeline setup as the biggest time sink per new client; automating it from 45 to 12 minutes is a concrete, demonstrable value"},{"step":"Feature scope","decision":"Include proposals and e-signature in P1, not MVP","reason":"Core workflow (timeline, vendors, budget, client portal) must be rock solid before adding sales workflow; proposals are nice-to-have in first 90 days"},{"step":"Pricing","decision":"$55/$79/$95 tiers","reason":"$55 undercuts Aisle Planner''s $49 minimum while offering more; $79 Pro is the revenue target tier; $95 Studio captures studio owners"},{"step":"Technical","decision":"Rule-based timeline engine over ML","reason":"The milestone library approach is deterministic, explainable, and editable; ML recommendations would require extensive training data we don''t have at launch"},{"step":"Trial strategy","decision":"60-day free trial, no credit card required","reason":"Planners are cautious adopters; extended free trial removes risk perception and allows them to onboard a real wedding before committing to payment"},{"step":"GTM","decision":"Target recently certified planners (ABC, WIPA certifications) via association email lists","reason":"Newly certified planners don''t have entrenched tool habits yet; they are the highest-conversion cohort for new software adoption"}]',
    'submitted', 29, NOW() - INTERVAL '12 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '13 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '12 days');

