-- IDEA 19: Auto-post Social Media Scheduler (cancelled) - Author 9
-- ============================================================
(19, 9, E'# QueuedUp - The "Set It and Forget It" Social Scheduler for Local Businesses\n\n## 1. Executive Summary\n\nQueuedUp is a social media scheduling platform built around a single workflow: batch-load content once a week, let QueuedUp handle the rest. Designed for local small businesses — restaurants, salons, gyms, boutiques, contractors — who know they need to post consistently but have no time or marketing expertise to do so daily. QueuedUp''s signature feature is the "Weekly Fill" mode: the owner spends 20 minutes every Sunday selecting and queuing posts; QueuedUp auto-distributes them at optimal times throughout the week.\n\n**Primary Insight**: Small business owners don''t fail at social media because they lack content ideas — they fail because the daily execution drains time they don''t have. QueuedUp moves the effort to one weekly session.\n\n## 2. Market Analysis\n\n| Metric | Data | Source |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| US small businesses (1-10 employees) | 6M | SBA 2023 |\n| SMBs managing own social media | 71% | Clutch |\n| SMBs with inconsistent posting (>2 week gap) | 58% | Sprout Social |\n| Avg hours/week on social media (SMB owners) | 6.1 hrs | Clutch |\n| Businesses willing to pay for scheduling tool | 43% | Hootsuite SMB survey |\n| Existing tool adoption rate | 22% | Hootsuite |\n| SMB social software market | ~$2.4B | Industry estimate |\n| Underserved "non-marketer" segment | ~$480M | ~20% of market |\n\n**Insight**: The 58% with inconsistent posting are not lazy — they have inconsistent time. Sunday batch-loading matches the natural rhythm of business owners who plan their week on weekends.\n\n## 3. Competitive Landscape\n\n| Competitor | Price/mo | Strength | Non-Marketer Friendly? |\n|-----------|----------|---------|------------------------|\n| Buffer | $6-$120 | Simple core UX | Partially |\n| Hootsuite | $49-$249 | Feature-complete | No |\n| Later | $18-$80 | Great visual planner | Partially |\n| Planoly | $17-$47 | Instagram-native | Partially |\n| Sked Social | $25-$159 | Auto-posting | No |\n| **QueuedUp** | **$17-$45** | **Weekly Fill workflow** | **Yes (primary focus)** |\n\n## 4. Target User Personas\n\n### Persona A: Diane - The Salon Owner\n- **Age**: 44, female, suburban Chicago\n- **Business**: Hair salon, 4 stylists, $380k revenue\n- **Social media**: Instagram + Facebook; posts when she remembers (1-2x/week at best)\n- **Pain**: Takes 30-45 min to create one post (choosing photo, writing caption, figuring out hashtags)\n- **Dream**: Upload 7 photos Sunday night, have one post go out each day that week\n- **Specific request from interviews**: "Can it write the caption for me? Or at least give me a starting point?"\n- **Willingness to pay**: $17-$25/month if setup is easy\n\n### Persona B: Tyler - The Landscaping Company Owner\n- **Age**: 38, male, Phoenix AZ\n- **Business**: Landscaping + irrigation, 8 employees, seasonal\n- **Social media**: Knows he should be on Instagram to show before/afters but hasn''t started\n- **Pain**: Starting from zero is overwhelming; doesn''t know what to post or when\n- **Need**: Industry-specific post ideas + a simple queue system\n- **Willingness to pay**: $17/month if it helps him get started\n\n### Persona C: Priya - The Independent Nutritionist\n- **Age**: 31, female, online business\n- **Social media**: Active on Instagram (2,100 followers) and starting to use LinkedIn\n- **Pain**: Has great content ideas but keeps forgetting to post; loses engagement momentum during busy client weeks\n- **Need**: A content calendar she can fill when inspired (sometimes 3 posts in one day) that drips them out automatically\n- **Willingness to pay**: $25-$35/month for multi-platform + analytics\n\n## 5. Core Features\n\n| Priority | Feature | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| P0 | Weekly Fill mode | 20-minute guided session to queue 7 days of content |\n| P0 | Post composer | Photo/video upload, caption editor, platform selector |\n| P0 | Auto-distribution | Posts go out at system-recommended optimal times |\n| P0 | Instagram + Facebook | Core platform support at launch |\n| P0 | Mobile app (PWA) | Phone-first; batch upload from camera roll |\n| P1 | Caption starter suggestions | Industry-detected starters: "Behind the scenes...", "Did you know..." |\n| P1 | Google Business Profile | Post business updates + offers |\n| P1 | Content recycler | Mark posts as "evergreen" to re-queue after 60 days |\n| P1 | Posting calendar | Monthly view of all scheduled content |\n| P2 | AI caption generation | Describe the image → get 3 caption options |\n| P2 | Engagement metrics | Likes, reach, comments per post |\n| P2 | Hashtag suggestions | Relevant hashtags based on post content and industry |\n\n## 6. Technical Architecture\n\n```\nCore Architecture:\n\nFrontend:\n  - Next.js 15 + TailwindCSS\n  - PWA manifest for homescreen install\n  - Drag-and-drop weekly calendar (dnd-kit)\n  - Mobile-optimized batch upload (camera roll access via File API)\n\nBackend:\n  - Go + Echo v4\n  - Post scheduler: Redis queue + worker goroutines\n  - Platform integrations:\n    - Instagram Graph API (requires Facebook Business Manager)\n    - Facebook Pages API\n    - Google Business Profile API\n  - Rate limit manager: Per-platform API quota tracking\n\nData:\n  - PostgreSQL 16 (users, posts, schedules, platform tokens)\n  - Redis (job queue, token cache, rate limit counters)\n  - Cloudflare R2 (media storage)\n\nAuth:\n  - Email/password (owner account)\n  - OAuth 2.0 per platform (Instagram, Facebook, Google)\n\nAI:\n  - OpenAI GPT-4o-mini for caption generation (P2)\n  - Industry detection from business profile tags\n```\n\n## 7. Business Model\n\n| Plan | Price | Profiles | Posts/Mo | Features |\n|------|-------|----------|---------|----------|\n| Free | $0 | 1 | 10 | Basic scheduling, Instagram only |\n| Starter | $17/mo | 3 | 50 | + Facebook, Google, content recycler |\n| Growth | $35/mo | 6 | 200 | + Analytics, AI captions, hashtags |\n| Pro | $45/mo | 10 | Unlimited | + Priority support, team member |\n\n**Business model note**: Free tier is a genuine user acquisition channel, not a crippled product. 10 posts/month is enough to prove value before paying.\n\n## 8. MVP Roadmap\n\n| Milestone | Duration | Focus | Gate |\n|-----------|----------|-------|------|\n| M1: Core queue | 5 weeks | Weekly Fill, post composer, Instagram, Facebook | 15 beta users, 5+ posts/week avg |\n| M2: Distribution | 3 weeks | Auto-timing, calendar view, Google Business | Posts going out on time 99%+ |\n| M3: Retention tools | 4 weeks | Content recycler, caption starters, PWA | 30-day retention ≥50% |\n| M4: Growth | 4 weeks | AI captions, billing, referral program | 60 paid users |\n\n## 9. Success Metrics\n\n| KPI | 3-Month | 6-Month |\n|-----|---------|--------|\n| Registered users | 400 | 1,200 |\n| Paid subscribers | 100 | 400 |\n| MRR | $2,800 | $11,500 |\n| Avg posts/user/week | ≥4 | ≥5 |\n| Weekly Fill mode adoption | ≥60% of active users | ≥70% |\n| 30-day user retention | ≥50% | ≥58% |\n| NPS | ≥42 | ≥50 |\n\n## 10. Risks & Mitigation\n\n| Risk | Severity | Probability | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|-------------|------------|\n| Instagram API changes break scheduling | High | Medium | Monitor API changelog weekly; maintain Facebook fallback; user notification system |\n| Weekly Fill habit doesn''t stick | High | Medium | In-app Sunday reminder (push notification); 3-week streak reward |\n| Users don''t connect social accounts during signup | High | High | Mandatory platform connection in onboarding; can''t access scheduler without at least 1 connection |\n| Content creation (not scheduling) remains the real blocker | Medium | High | Ship AI captions as P1, not P2; test in beta with select users immediately |\n| Market perceived as commoditized (Buffer exists) | Medium | Medium | "Weekly Fill" workflow is the differentiator; market it as a workflow product not a features comparison |',
    E'[{"step":"Signature feature","decision":"Weekly Fill mode as the defining product mechanic","reason":"Reduces social media to one 20-minute weekly session; this is a concrete, marketable promise that Buffer and Hootsuite don''t make"},{"step":"Free tier","decision":"Genuine free tier with 10 posts/month","reason":"Competing against free tools (Facebook Business Suite) requires a free option; 10 posts/month is enough to form a habit before converting"},{"step":"Mobile priority","decision":"PWA as primary mobile experience, not native app","reason":"85% of small business owner social media management happens from phones; PWA delivers the needed experience without app store delays and fees"},{"step":"AI captions","decision":"Promote to P1 priority based on beta feedback signal","reason":"Every persona interview indicated caption writing as the primary friction point, not scheduling; solving the content problem unlocks the scheduling behavior"},{"step":"Sunday timing","decision":"Market and design around Sunday batch-loading ritual","reason":"Business owners naturally plan their week on Sunday; matching product design to an existing behavior pattern reduces adoption friction"},{"step":"Platform focus","decision":"Instagram + Facebook at launch, Google Business as P1","reason":"Meta platforms cover the majority of small business social activity; adding Google Business in P1 addresses the underused local SEO opportunity most owners overlook"}]',
    'submitted', 22, NOW() - INTERVAL '19 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '20 days', NOW() - INTERVAL '19 days');

